A few men, sir?

1034
01:26:23,120 --> 01:26:26,080
Contact at 2,500 yards.

1035
01:26:26,160 --> 01:26:27,360
Might cross the stern.

1036
01:26:27,440 --> 01:26:29,640
We'll wait... right here.

1037
01:26:32,400 --> 01:26:35,920
Wallace... no matter what
Mr. Brice says,

1038
01:26:36,000 --> 01:26:37,600
I want you to go
to the radio shack

1039
01:26:37,640 --> 01:26:40,200
and establish a voice contact
with that ship immediately.

1040
01:26:40,280 --> 01:26:41,600
You are not the skipper
of this ship, Mr. O'Dell!

1041
01:26:41,640 --> 01:26:43,520
And neither are you, sir!

1042
01:27:10,640 --> 01:27:12,400
Rain squall.

1043
01:27:14,600 --> 01:27:16,960
With a little luck, they
won't see us in all this...

1044
01:27:17,000 --> 01:27:19,080
...weather.

1045
01:27:46,640 --> 01:27:47,920
Here!

1046
01:27:48,000 --> 01:27:49,840
Please!

1047
01:27:49,920 --> 01:27:51,440
We're over here!

1048
01:27:51,520 --> 01:27:54,320
Please!

1049
01:27:54,400 --> 01:27:56,400
Help, please!

1050
01:27:56,480 --> 01:27:58,000
Help!

1051
01:27:58,080 --> 01:28:00,200
On your starboard side!

1052
01:28:06,000 --> 01:28:08,640
It's really not safe up here,
Miss Page.

1053
01:28:13,640 --> 01:28:16,240
We're going below now!

1054
01:28:16,320 --> 01:28:17,680
Aah!

1055
01:28:23,040 --> 01:28:25,520
Bury everybody
and bury the truth...

1056
01:28:25,600 --> 01:28:27,040
is that it, Brice?!

1057
01:28:29,720 --> 01:28:31,400
Like this.

1058
01:28:31,480 --> 01:28:33,680
This is how I go.

1059
01:28:36,040 --> 01:28:38,040
If that's your plan...

1060
01:28:38,120 --> 01:28:40,760
get on with it,
you fucking coward!

1061
01:28:48,000 --> 01:28:51,120
Stumbo, man the ports.
Get ready to scuttle this boat!

1062
01:28:52,760 --> 01:28:53,960
Just leave!

1063
01:28:54,040 --> 01:28:55,800
They'll blame it on a U-boat!

1064
01:28:57,280 --> 01:29:00,040
Just get out of here!
They'll never fuckin' know!

1065
01:29:00,120 --> 01:29:01,800
Any more advice for me, champ?

1066
01:29:14,280 --> 01:29:16,440
500 yards and closing!

1067
01:29:16,520 --> 01:29:18,480
Looks like we're definitely
gonna lose some paint

1068
01:29:18,560 --> 01:29:19,600
on this one, sir!

1069
01:29:19,680 --> 01:29:22,640
I kept looking for some way
just...

1070
01:29:22,720 --> 01:29:25,800
just to... take it back,

1071
01:29:25,880 --> 01:29:27,880
to make it end right...

1072
01:29:27,960 --> 01:29:31,160
some way without
dishonoring Winters.

1073
01:29:35,520 --> 01:29:38,560
I was gonna wear this uniform
back to port.

1074
01:29:39,880 --> 01:29:41,760
Now...

1075
01:29:47,400 --> 01:29:49,440
What should I do, Miss Page?

1076
01:29:49,480 --> 01:29:52,720
You give me the light
so that I can signal for help.

1077
01:29:52,800 --> 01:29:54,080
I don't...

1078
01:29:55,880 --> 01:29:57,840
God, I don't know!

1079
01:30:33,400 --> 01:30:35,920
I just figured out
why he didn't kill me, too.

1080
01:30:36,920 --> 01:30:38,320
He didn't have to.

1081
01:30:56,680 --> 01:30:59,960
Aah!

1082
01:31:21,880 --> 01:31:25,000
Hey! Over here!

1083
01:31:25,080 --> 01:31:26,640
Come back!

1084
01:31:26,760 --> 01:31:29,400
Come back.

1085
01:32:32,520 --> 01:32:37,240
Well, you weren't the first
woman that ever slapped me,

1086
01:32:37,320 --> 01:32:39,320
and you won't be the last.

1087
01:32:39,400 --> 01:32:42,320
But that was a good thing
you done for me back there.

1088
01:32:44,160 --> 01:32:45,440
Well done, Miss Page.

1089
01:32:48,480 --> 01:32:51,120
Well done, Mr. Stumbo.

1090
01:32:53,000 --> 01:32:55,720
Dead but not buried, I see.

1091
01:32:58,720 --> 01:32:59,640
Pardon me?

1092
01:32:59,720 --> 01:33:01,320
Your vessel.

1093
01:33:31,120 --> 01:33:35,440
So, what would you say
if you had to explain it all?

1094
01:33:36,480 --> 01:33:39,040
Does seem rather unlikely now,
doesn't it?

1095
01:33:41,960 --> 01:33:44,160
Have you thought that...

1096
01:33:44,200 --> 01:33:46,080
that maybe
when Captain Winters died,

1097
01:33:46,120 --> 01:33:49,760
he just... died, and that was it?

1098
01:33:49,800 --> 01:33:51,680
And the rest...

1099
01:33:53,200 --> 01:33:55,080
And the rest...

1100
01:33:56,520 --> 01:33:57,800
I don't know.

1101
01:34:00,840 --> 01:34:03,680
You say whatever
you have to say, ensign.

1102
01:34:04,880 --> 01:34:08,560
I'll always believe we were
brought back here for a reason.

